id: pm-g9xk
title: "GH-443: lean error mode — drop constant required/why boilerplate from structured errors"
description: "Dogfood GH-443: every structured error carries two constant prose fields (required/why) that never vary by error; keep only actionable fields in lean mode. Duplicate check: pm-gdi7 covers unknown-option suggestions, not envelope size; no other overlap."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:cli",gh-issue,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-07-06T08:03:05.997Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-15T19:27:27.234Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: JSON errors omit generic constant prose while keeping code/detail/examples/next_steps/recovery; error-envelope spec updated; mode documented for agents
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: low
confidence: high
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-gdi7,related,"2026-07-06T08:03:05.997Z",null,null
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-15T19:27:27.232Z",maintainer-agent,"Fresh evidence 2026-07-15 (review pass #89): a one-token command typo (pm lst) returns ~20 lines / ~150 tokens of constant scaffolding (What happened / What is required / Why / Examples / Next steps / Recovery bundle) around the only two load-bearing lines: the error name and \"Did you mean: list?\". Worse, for unknown-OPTION errors the Error: headline and the \"What happened:\" paragraph are the IDENTICAL sentence twice (observed on --statuss). Lean mode should collapse to headline + suggestion + one recovery hint; the full bundle stays behind --verbose or a config key. Duplicate-sentence dedup is worth doing even before lean mode ships."
body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/443\n\n## Problem\nThe structured error envelope carries two constant-prose fields on every error (`required`: \"Use values that match documented command constraints.\"; `why`: \"Validation protects data consistency...\"). They never vary by error and carry no actionable signal — pure token overhead in retry loops.\n\n## Proposed fix\nLean error mode (or simply omit constant `why`/`required` under --json unless error-specific): keep `code`, `detail`, `examples`, `next_steps`, `recovery.suggested_retry`. Verbose prose stays for human/TTY.\n\n## Definition of done\nJSON errors drop generic boilerplate (or --lean-errors/PM_LEAN_ERRORS added); error-envelope spec updated; agent docs note the mode. Related: pm-gdi7 covers unknown-option did-you-mean in the same envelope."
